casebody.data:
McKay, Respondent, v. Brewster, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. May 7, 1890.)

Argued before Labremore, C. J., and Bookstaver, J.

Chas. E. Le Barbiere, for appellant. Thomas D. Rambaut, for respondent.

No opinion. Motion to strike case from calendar denied, with $10 costs.
